qas.question: What comprises the standard pronunciation of Catalan?
Where are the most speakers found?
In what densely populated area is it spoken?
What part of the province of Tarragona is Central Catalan spoken?

context: <a0_0><a1_0>Central Catalan<a1_0/><a0_0/> is considered the standard pronunciation of the language and has the highest number of speakers. It is spoken in the densely populated regions of the <a2_0>Barcelona province<a2_0/>, the <a3_0>eastern half<a3_0/> of the province of Tarragona, and most of the province of Girona.
